save plot to temp

Source: R/graphics_helpers.R
ft_plot_temp_file.Rd

Take a plot object (default is ggplot2::last_plot()), and write it to a file that can be easily found and opened in a VSCode editor pane for a zoomed view of the plot.

Usage

ft_plot_temp_file(
  in_plot = ggplot2::last_plot(),
  filename = "_deleteme_plot.png",
  width = 10,
  height = 8,
  units = "in",
  res = 300,
  ...
)

Arguments

in_plot

the plot to save

filename

the file to save it to. Default is underscore to make it easily findable

width

width of the saved plot

height

height of the saved plot

units

units to use

res

the resolution

...

other parameters to ragg::agg_png()

Value

filename

See also

ragg::agg_png()
